 href=\"http://www.duluthtrading.com\">Duluth Trading Company</a>. The Duluth Pack was borne as a portage pack for canoes, a key mode of transport and modern day state hobby in the Boundary Waters. These beautifully crafted satchels are so amazing, I\'m dedicating an entire post to the plethora of Minnesota exports I discovered on this journey. Duluth Trading Company will have their own section in said post as well in ode their incredible adventure pants as Andrew and I affectionately call them, and served perfectly for continued northbound journey. They also have a fantastic cabin building book selection. Before leaving town for the next leg of our journey, we stumbled onto a beautiful cookbook of an apparent local café and declared it our lunch spot.\r\n\r\nSuperior Street, Duluth along Lake Superior leads right into Bob Dylan Way, a.k.a. Highway 61. I loved old albums growing up and a framed copy of Highway 61 was prominently displayed in my Amagansett bedroom.\r\n\r\n<img class=\" wp-image-405 alignright\" src=\"http://maidstonebuttermilk.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/07/DSC001661-293x450.jpg\" alt=\"DSC00166\" width=\"195\" height=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYou can\'t go very far in Minnesota without being reminded of it\'s strong Nordic and Scandinavian heritage.\r\n\r\nPictured here: a statue of Lief Ericson, an Icelandic explorer, known as the first Norse explorer to reach America. The only other place I have seen a tall statue of Lief next to a Lutheran church and a body of water is in <a href=\"http://maidstonebuttermilk.com/reykjavik-cool-and-the-sudurland/\">Reykjavík</a>.\r\n\r\nBehind him is a vibrant and fragrant rose garden.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><em>Lief Ericson Statue</em> <span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">0</span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe took the County State Aid Hwy 61, a route along the water so scenic, it seemed a Robert Moses inspired PCH right in northern Minnesota. Across from the stood a one level building with large windows, wild gardens and several Adirondack chairs. We arrived at the <a href=\"http://www.sceniccafe.com\">New Scenic Café</a>.\r\n\r\nJazz that I like to call <em>Woody Allen </em>jazz – the kind of sound played at a fabulous cocktail party in a sophisticated city in his films – gently filled the restaurant. I sat next to a window overlooking a succulent garden and Lake Superior. The walls were of pine wainscoting and decorated with a local artist\'s depictions of horses. I sipped vetliner grüner and the meal that proceeded was one of the most splendid I can recall. Pistachio crusted goat cheese salad. Grilled walleye sandwich on crisp slices of homemade cranberry walnut bread. Tuna and avocado wantons with freshly made wasabi. A marzipan tart with chunks of rhubard sided with a local brew.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n+++\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nNew scenic cafe found from a coffee book. Forward by garrison Keiler. Quaint. William Sonoma jazz. Fresh, every food item made with intention. Flavors fresh. Everything you need umami.\r\n<div class=\"yj6qo ajU\">\r\n\r\n Ely\r\n\r\nNature hiking\r\nLIFE MILESTONES\r\nBeautiful canoe ride\r\nWild rice paddies\r\nStars so bright you can see their reflection in the lake.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n• Minnesota traveling Duluth/Ely and our story\r\n○ Minneapolis\r\n§ Modern Times - tattoos\r\n§ Foundry ?\r\n§ Hunt and Gather\r\n§ More foundry on 1st\r\n§ Marvel; awesome other store; TBF -- all one owner\r\n□ Bachelor Farmer: sweet corn, red herring caught in Lake Superior, homemade ginger cookies; heart wallpaper; exposed beam &amp; wainscoting; exposed ducts-- at Marvel delighted in SuperDry seltzer cocktail and smoky …, store with cool poster of Poliça upcoming performance\r\nYankees vs twins\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','In Search of Lake Wobegon: Adventures in Minnesota','','inherit','open','open','','393-revision-v1','','','2015-07-31 07:47:28','2015-07-31 11:47:28','',393,'http://maidstonebuttermilk.com/393